        "text": "Justice, and judgment, and equity; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " which teach men just judgment or equity, to wit, their whole duty, both to God and to others, and to themselves. These three words seem to signify the same thing, and are heaped together to note either the necessity of the precept, or the exactness and diligence which is required in the practice of it. ",
